The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the two-center problem in the Euclidean plane. This problem involves finding the smallest radius for two congruent disks that cover a set of points in the plane. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also introduces new techniques for dynamically maintaining circular hulls under point insertions and deletions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which could place it in cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
